    "updated_at": "2016-02-24T00:33:53Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "There are many options for distributed RPC where you can have a queue, a poll, a pub/sub, pipeline with fusion steps, and with some of these you don't need a timeout and just have an exponential retry if the message is not received based on the design topology.  For broker-less implementations of multiple directory-service registered queues among the clients that do the work to ensure the messages are properly received/sent.  So many options, it just depends what you are designing it for and the target applications.\n"
  },
