    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "As a datapoint, for the Objective-C client, timeouts are optional; and we want to discourage people from setting them (because the experience is they tend to set values that work great in the US, but are too low for slower networks in developing countries). The datacenter use case obviously differs.\n"
